President Obama thanks Dr. Rebecca Blank for her hard work and exceptional service during her time at the Department of Commerce. He praises her as a steady leader and a vital member of his economic team. Blank has been a tireless advocate for American businesses, helping to increase competitiveness, support innovators and entrepreneurs, and bring jobs back to the United States. Although the President is sad to see her go, he wishes her the best of luck in her new role as chancellor of the University of Wisconsin Badgers.